		<title>06Hindlip CE First School</title>
		<content> Situated in Fernhill Heath, this 5 to 
 9 school serves the area north east of
 the railway in the village. With about
 80 children on roll, its numbers have 
 fallen in recent years. The school    
 building was originally a chapel built
 as a satellite church to St.          
 John's, Claines. It lies at a         
 dangerous part of the A38 and there   
 are plans for a replacement school to 
 be constructed at some time in the    
 future.                               
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
